  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (d3d8c0b 2022-12-24T18:56:59.4932843Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge script\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nWindows\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nIn a very recent release, the vm.writeFile() cheatcode stopped working in scripts. It still works in tests.\r\n\r\nI'm still investigating which release broke it. \r\n\r\nThis doesn't work:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.17;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Script.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract WriteScript is Script {\r\n\r\n    string filepath = \"script/hello_world.txt\";\r\n\r\n    function run() external {\r\n        vm.writeFile(filepath, \"hello world!\");\r\n        string memory data = vm.readFile(filepath);\r\n        console.log(data);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis works fine:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.17;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract WriteTest is Test {\r\n\r\n    string filepath = \"test/hello_world.txt\";\r\n\r\n    function testWrite() external {\r\n        vm.writeFile(filepath, \"hello world!\");\r\n        string memory data = vm.readFile(filepath);\r\n        assertEq(data, \"hello world!\");\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
